  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Vikram Bakshi and Others versus R.P. Khosla and Another pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_8_1444_1463','2025INSC1020'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VIKRAM BAKSHI AND OTHERS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>R.P. KHOSLA AND ANOTHER </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 1444</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1020</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006472025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH</strong><br> 1444 : 2025 INSC 1020 Vikram Bakshi and Others v. R.P. Khosla and Another (Criminal Appeal No. 3646 of 2025) 20 August 2025 [B.R. Gavai, CJI and Augustine George Masih,* J.] Issue for Consideration Whether a review or recall of an order passed in a criminal proceeding initiated under section 340 petition filed u/s.340 against the appellants for prosecution of offences of perjury and directed that the said application be listed for hearing: Held: As envisaged under the CrPC, criminal courts are barred from altering or review their own judgments except for the exceptions explicitly provided<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 20-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3646/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_8_1444_1463','2025INSC1020','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2